# Reading Notes for CSS

[Article for CSS, What is CSS?]("https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/CSS/First_steps/What_is_CSS")
[Second article, How to add CSS]("https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_howto.asp")
[Link for Color page with ex]("https://www.w3schools.com/cssref/pr_text_color.asp")

- first link has examples of how to background color and border color
- CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) allows you to create great-looking web pages, it is the styling side of your webpage
- It can be used for changing color, size, of headings or links, background border colors
- {} and inside will have multiple declarations such as color font
-  
- 3 times are external CSS internal CSS and inline CSS
- An external style sheet can be written in any text editor, and must be saved with a .css extension. The external .css file should not contain any HTML tags.
- An internal style sheet may be used if one single HTML page has a unique style. The internal style is defined inside the <style> element, inside the head section.
- An inline style may be used to apply a unique style for a single element. To use inline styles, add the style attribute to the relevant element. The style attribute
  can contain any CSS property
  - All the styles in a page will "cascade" into a new "virtual" style sheet by the following rules, where number one has the highest priority:

-This is order of importance and priorirty 
 1. Inline style (inside an HTML element)
 2. External and internal style sheets (in the head section)
 3. Browser default
